# Resolve.AI Secure Credentials Configuration

# To enable real live Google OAuth:
# 1. Create a project on the Google Developer Console (https://console.cloud.google.com)
# 2. Configure OAuth consent screen and create an OAuth 2.0 Client ID for Web Applications
# 3. Add 'http://localhost:5173/login' to the Authorized Redirect URIs
# 4. Copy your Client ID and replace the value below:
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=YOUR_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID.apps.googleusercontent.com

# To enable real live Facebook OAuth:
# 1. Register as a developer on Facebook (https://developers.facebook.com)
# 2. Create a new App and select 'Facebook Login' settings
# 3. Add 'http://localhost:5173/login' to the Valid OAuth Redirect URIs
# 4. Copy your App ID and replace the value below:
VITE_FACEBOOK_APP_ID=YOUR_FACEBOOK_APP_ID
